    comments: "Stays true to the low-budget horror movie feel, but is pretty good with its mix of practical effects and subtle ways to make Iris who she is"
  }
  makeup {
    rating: "Decent to Pretty Good"
    comments: "Mainly for Iris as her hairstyle made her feel very 50s and subserviant, something that her 'boyfriend' was trying to make her look as"
  }
  costumes {
    rating: "Decent to Pretty Good"
    comments: "Mainly for Iris as her costumes made her feel very 50s and subserviant, something that her 'boyfriend' was trying to make her look as"
  }
  pacing: "Pacing is fine as the movie uses its runtime effectively"
  climax: "Climax is executed well as it is full of twists and turns you do not expect; the ending makes this movie come together full circle"
  tone: "Tone is very genre-less as it combines black comedy, drama, thriller, and horror elements"
  final_notes: "Telugu was mentioned (but probably not for a good reason); Saw this an 'AMC Scream-Unseen' and that was the way to see it because this is very much a mystery movie that you should go in blind (especially because the trailer and poster gives nothing)"
  overall: "Overall, a pretty good horror movie that feels very genre-less; the film's unpredictable story, brought to life by Sophie Thatcher and Jack Quaid's performances, effectively uses its 'mystery' premise to explore female indepedence; I saw this movie as an 'AMC Scream-Unseen' and that was honestly the way to see it because this is very much a mystery movie that you should go in blind"
